// bisect: The `check` oracle (interp vs jit) reports AGREE — both produce Value(true). The divergence is Fused-vs-others, visible only in `run` mode: Interp=Value(true), Jit=Value(true), but Fused (gir_interp) CRASHES the tokio worker → RuntimeErr(runtime died). Stable across 5 runs.
// interp/jit: Confirmed reproducing and deterministic. `run` mode: Interp=Value(true), Jit=Value(true), Fused crashes with panic at gir_interp.rs:1225 'DynCall arg shape mismatch: declared Error, got DateTime(Error(I64(0)))'. Reproduced identically 5x (3 repeats + isolation variants). Program uses only error() an
// root_cause: Two coupled sites in graphix-compiler/src/gir_interp.rs. (1) wrap_value_shape (lines 843-849) routes GirType::Error through its `_ => EvalResult::DateTime(v)` catch-all, so error(0) is carried as EvalResult::DateTime(Value::Error(..)) — fine for produce/return because into_value() ignores the carrier. (2) The DynCall arg-marshalling match (lines 1198-1228) lists the value-shape declared types as `GirType::DateTime | Duration | Bytes | Map` (lines 1201-1205) but OMITS GirType::Error. When the is_err(e) DynCall arrives with a declared arg type of GirType::Error and an EvalResult::DateTime carrie

{let e = error(0); is_err(e)}
